results.title: With Friends Like These...
results.description: Stark learns from Black Widow that a spy is intent on Starting WW III.

results.title: War Games
results.description: With US missiles flying, Iron Man has to avert nuclear war and learn why Black Widow initiated the launch.

results.title: Decisions In A Vacuum
results.description: A designated group of Avengers (including Iron Man) enter a Kree space station in an attempt to negotiate peace with the Kree and the Shi'ar. The Avengers run into some Shi'ar commandos in which they battle, and Iron Man ends up battling a Kree soldier named Shatterax (who was sent by the Supreme Intelligence) outside the station. Iron Man ends up deciding to surrender the Avenger team over to the Kree in hopes of survival.

results.title: Put the Hammer Down!
results.description: Tony Stark, in the War Machine armor, and the Masters of Silence invade Hammer's stronghold.

results.title: Ground Zero
results.description: The government intervenes with Firepower to stop Atom Smasher from destroying a toxic waste dump.

results.title: Soul on Ice
results.description: While Stark dreams of his past in suspended animation, scientists inject him with a tailored virus to rebuild his nervous system.

results.title: Save the People, Save the Country
This Year's Model
results.description: Bed ridden Stark controls his new armor remotely to stop an assault on a Stark Enterprises Facility.

results.title: Neuromimetic Telepresence Unit Overview
results.description: Technical drawings and specifications for Iron Man's new remote controled armor.

results.title: Mixed Reactions
results.description: Iron Man is attacked by Berserker 7.  It is hinted that Berserker is a vessel for someone with a score to settle.

results.title: Controlling Interests
results.description: Tony Stark is abducted by the Controller, Basil Sandhurst.

results.title: Heart of Stone
results.description: Orgin story for the villian Earthmover.

results.title: Appetite for Destruction: Chapter 1
results.description: Jim Rhodes gathers associates of Tony Stark to suit up in the various versions of the Iron Man armor.

results.title: Chapter 2: The Soft Machine
results.description: Stark struggles to regain control of his nervous system, Veronica Benning bares her soul.

results.title: Chapter 3: The Iron Legion
results.description: The Iron Legion battles Ultimo.

results.title: Finale: Armored and Dangerous
results.description: Stark regains consciousness and suits up to join the battle with Ultimo.

results.title: Personnel Bios
results.description: Personnal bio's of the more visible personnel at Stark Enterprises.

results.title: Broadcast Storm
results.description: Stark Enterprises is implicated in scandal.

results.title: Will The Real Tony Stark Step Forward?
Terminal Emulation
results.description: VOR / TEX steals Stark's body --trapping Stark in Cyberspace-- then goes on a rampage.

results.title: Believe It Or Not, Iron Man IS The Winner!
Signal to Noise
results.description: Iron Man and VOR / TEX battle it out.  Veronica Benning leaves.  The Mandarin searches for rings of power.

results.title: Friends and Other Enemies
results.description: While The Mandarin prepares to re-emerge from solitude, Iron Man and War Machine duke it out.

results.title: The Conqueror
results.description: While The Mandarin tortures Iron Man, War Machine and Force Works battle Medieval Chinese warriors.

results.title: No Mercy! (Hands of The Mandarin [Part 6 of 6])
There Shall Come an Ending
results.description: The conclusion of the Hands of The Mandarin cross over arc.

results.title: Caught Up in the Holiday Spirits
Resolutions
results.description: Tony Stark attends AA.

results.title: Old Soldiers
results.description: Prof. Ted Slaght is shown to have Alzheimer's Disease. Tony Stark speaks in Russia and eventually has a run in with Titanium Man.

results.title: Triangle
results.description: Iron Man continues his battle with Titanium Man and is assisted by the Black Widow and Crimson Dynamo. Prof. Ted Slaght is killed under his own laboratory accident caused by his Alzheimer's Disease. Roxxon subcontracts Mycroft Holmes to eliminate Stark Enterprises.

results.title: Strange Bedfellows
results.description: Tony Stark in the Crimson Dymano armor battles Titanium Man.

results.title: Brothers in Arms
results.description: War Machine, U.S. Agent, and Hawkeye stand against the rest of Force Works during a rebel insurgency.

results.title: Hot Metal
results.description: Caught in a lab accident, Stark's mentor Ted Slaght becomes Slag and seeks revenge.

results.title: Shadows Call
results.description: Stark goes through agonizing re-evaluation.  Iron Man is confronted by the Scarlet Witch.

results.title: Hollow Man
results.description: Stark is still trying to deal with personal and relationship problems.  Some interesting stuff in the background.
